title: For Sale/Trade:  Bust the Scammers
postcontent: There is a guy here, his number is 405-620-4341, look it up in the search armslist option to see all his ads, who has been selling ammo that he buys at walmart and academy in huge quantities and doubles or triples the price. He also has a bunch of ads on here that he posts the price as FREE, then when you click on his ad, the price is shown for what he is selling. He is a scam artist and is one of the guys who will get armslist shut down. he lists a bunch of guns for salle and does not have an FFL. The law states that without an FFL, an individual is allowed to sell a "reasonable" number of guns per year. As a former FFL holder, I am quite aware that beyond 5 guns/ year, the ATF takes notice, this guy lists dozens if not hundreds of guns per year here. he is also the one running the ad, "Need Money, I buy guns". He is about to cause a world of hurt to armslist and it affects all of us. I urge you to flag his free and ammo ads, and take the time to look at his other ads by clicking the option in blue "listings by this user". It's time we stand together, protect our rights, protect armslist, and shut down the abusers, thieves, and scammers. Let your voice be heard by flagging the abusers. I'm an old Marine, and have learned to not go looking for trouble, but there are times when it's necessary to get up on the hood of the old jeep and sound off.The market and system will take care of abusers. If people stop buying from or selling to an abuser, they move on. With our gun rights in such a precarious balance, it's best to handle things on our own, within the law, create as few waves as possible, and let the market take care of itself. Get the word out, educate people, and remember, Knowledge is power.

title: For Sale:  Adams Arms AR15 Gas Piston Conversion Kit - Mid-length (AR, ar15, colt, bushmaster, dpms, rock, armalite, s&w, daniel, stag, lmt, lwrc, sig, ruger, pws, hk, Hogan, Barrett, trijicon, eotech, noveske)
postcontent:
Adams Arms Gas Piston Conversion Kit for all AR15 Mid-length uppers. Makes Rifle Run Cooler & Cleaner With Less Felt Recoil !!! Less prone to failures due to dirty gas system like standard AR15 rifles. 

Kit has everything you need to replace the standard gas system in your AR-15 and convert it to a reliable, positive-cycling, gas piston system. Eliminates venting of hot gases and powder residue into the bolt carrier and receiver for reduced fouling and less wear on the action. Feeds more smoothly, maintenance is easier, and the gun runs cooler, too. Short-stroke piston shaft eliminates concussive gas expansion in the upper receiver for less violent cycling and reduced felt recoil. Easy to adjust for three levels of gas release: normal fire, firing with a suppressor attached, or a single round fired without cycling. Installation requires removal of original gas block, but no permanent alterations to barrel or upper receiver. Remove the piston system at any time and reinstall the original parts. Low profile gas piston block will allow the use of a free-float rail. 

This piston kit was removed from a brand new gun I bought and has never been fired or used. Comes with the gas block, piston assembly including op-rod, and bolt carrier. Just install a bolt of your caliber of choice in the carrier and it's ready to rock and roll. Why spend $1000-1400 or more on an entire gas piston upper when you can turn your current upper into a piston setup? These retail for $350, so my loss is your gain!

The stopping power of the AF2011-A1 is tremendous: 2 bullets for a total of 460 Grains weight impacting at 1 to 2 inches apart (depending on the distance of the target) will knock down a bull, while the whole 18 bullets, for a payload exceeding 4000 Grains, can be delivered to the target in about 3 seconds. The AF2011-A1 obviously features a number of very special parts, such as the single slide, the single frame, the single spur double hammer, the single grip safety, the single body double mainspring housing and the single double cavity magazine floor plate, the long and double magazine latch, the special barrel bushings and the hold open lever and side lever safety with long shafts: but the most interesting feature of the new pistol which we strived to keep during the development of the project, is the interchangeability of most internal parts, which come as standard 1911 replacement parts. These include the firing pins, the firing pins plates, the sears groups, the triple springs, the inner parts of the mainspring housings, the recoil springs and recoil springs rods, the magazine bodies and inner parts, the sights (including after market adjustable sights) the grips and grips screws and bushings.

*Dawson fiber optic front sight
*Dawson fiber optic adjustable rear sight
*Powder River Precision grip enhancement (grip tape)
*Factory XD Gear, including holster, mag pouch and mag loader

Gun is in good condition; it was well cared for and used by the original owner to shoot IPSC for a few years before she upgraded to an XDm 5.25. I bought it for my wife, but she lost interest (okay, she never really had any interest) and I don't shoot 9mm.

The magazines shown in the picture are high capacity and not legal in Massachusetts.  Mass compliant mags for this gun are ready available online or in gun shops, or you can purchase and modify high capacity magazines.

Asking $795 O.B.O. This is priced below cost without the Massachusetts markup.  Those familiar with this gun know the quality of these upgrades, and how hard ithe gun is to find in Massachusetts. Terms are cash, FTF on an FA-10 in the greater Boston/metrowest area. Buyer must have MA LTC-A.  All laws to be followed.

PLEASE read the terms below.  If you contact me, either tell me "I'll take it," or make me an offer, or ask me a question.  I hate responding to "is it still available?" emails or "call me" emails that end up being a waste of time.

I will listen to offers for trades, but the only trades I'm potentially interested in are a Beretta CX4 Storm carbine (9mm, 92FS mags), a Kriss Vector or a USGI M1 Carbine (IBM or Rockola).

*****

Standard Terms:
I am not a firearms dealer engaged in the business of buying and selling guns, I am merely a collector who occasionally sells a firearm from his personal collection.

All local, state and Federal laws are to be strictly followed. For those who are unsure of how to conduct a private transaction, I'm happy to answer questions and walk you through the process. However, any requests to violate the law will immediately end negotiations.

I prefer to conduct the majority of negotiations over PM, email or text. I'm not trying to be elusive, I just prefer a written record of our agreement.

I am happy to answer any and all questions to be best of my ability, however, please do your own research - I'm not a salesman.

All negotiations are to be conducted via email, text or phone call before the transaction. Once we reach a deal, negotiations are closed. If you show up to the transaction after we've made a deal and try to weasel another $50 out of me, I'll walk away.

You cannot "try it out" to see if you like the gun. I am not a walking show room. If we happen to be at the same range at the same time, and I have the gun that's for sale with me, I'll probably be willing to let you to try it out, but this is the exception, not the rule.

I cannot stress this one enough: when we reach an agreement (which could be as simple as "I'll take it" and "it's yours,") you've entered into a contract to complete the transaction. Unless the item is not as described (I take pains to make sure I fairly describe anything I sell, and I'll allow you all the time and leeway you need to inspect it), you're expected to show up when and where we agree and complete the transaction.

I reserve the right to sell to whomever I wish.

Please don't write "call me" with nothing else in your email. I'm not going to call you if I have no indication of your level of interest, if you want to make an offer, or what your questions might be.

Please don't ask, "Is it still available? with nothing else in your email. That's just a waste of everyone's time.

I reserve the right to ignore ridiculous offers.

to provide maximum wear characteristics then Parkerized to eliminate rusting.

The barrels on these are made from 4140 cold rolled steel and are rated at a barrel life of approximately 150,000 rounds. They are very top end.

postcontent:
LWRC M6A2 AR-15 with 16" barrel. The M6A2 rifle’s edge in capability, reliability, accuracy and long service life is the result of advanced technology materials and manufacturing processes, combined with progressive patented designs. All LWRCI carbine systems feature their short-stroke gas-piston operating system. The operating system is lightweight, self-regulating, and self-scraping. This system of operation does not foul the moving parts of the weapon with carbon or heat, greatly enhancing service life and reliability while decreasing both user and armorer maintenance. M6A2 rifles feature a match grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown. The barrel is treated with NiCorr surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon. As in all of LWRCI's rifles, the bolt carrier group of the M6A2 rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.

The 16" barrel is Cold Hammer Forged and NiCorr treated with a 1:7" twist rate. This rifle has a 9" lightweight quad rail handguard and low profile gas block. The butt stock is a B5 SOPMOD and the pistol grip is a MagPul MIAD. The sights are LWRC folding BUIS.
